## ⚙️ Context Parameters Configuration

### GLOBAL
```
We are working on a software development project for Westbrook Community Library,
a public library serving 45,000 residents across 1 central building and 2 branch
locations, managed by 12 staff members with a limited municipal budget.

The system to be designed is a centralized Reservation Management System to replace
the current manual process of paper logbooks, phone calls and informal emails.

The system must manage reservations for study rooms, meeting halls, projectors,
laptops and shared equipment across all three locations.
```

### REQUIREMENTS
```
- Usable by non-technical staff with basic computer literacy.
- Accessible from existing computers at each branch via a standard web browser.
- No proprietary client software installation required.
- Very limited municipal budget.
- Must support at least 3 simultaneous locations.
- Must handle rooms and shared equipment as reservable resources.
- Role-based access: Administrator, Staff User, Patron.
- Must be available during all library operating hours (99% uptime).
- Must prevent double-bookings automatically.
- Must support reporting and audit trail.
- No prolonged downtime or complex data migration.
```

### CURRENT CONTEXT
```
The Functional Analysis (v1.0) and User Stories (v1.0) have been completed.
We are now in the Technical Design and Technology Proposal phase of the SDLC.
The deliverable is a complete Technical Design document including architecture
proposal, technology stack, data model, and deployment considerations.
Language: English.
```

### RULES
```
- Justify every technology choice against the project constraints
  (budget, usability, browser-based, limited infrastructure).
- Prefer open-source or low-cost solutions given the budget constraint.
- Keep the architecture simple and appropriate for a small-to-medium project.
- Do not over-engineer the solution.
- All components must be named and their responsibilities clearly described.
- The data model must cover all functional requirements.
- Do not generate code at this stage.
```

