## 💬 Prompt 1 — Architecture overview

```
Based on the Functional Analysis and User Stories in the open documents,
propose a high-level architecture for the Westbrook Community Library
Reservation Management System.

Include:
- Architecture style chosen (e.g. monolithic, layered, microservices)
  and justification for why it suits this project
- Main system components and their responsibilities
- How the three library locations will interact with the system
- High-level data flow between components

Do not propose specific technologies yet.
```

---

## 💬 Prompt 2 — Technology stack proposal

```
Based on the architecture proposed and the project constraints
(browser-based, limited budget, non-technical staff, existing hardware),
propose a full technology stack for the system.

For each technology choice provide:
- Layer (Frontend / Backend / Database / Infrastructure)
- Technology name
- Version or edition recommended
- Justification (why this technology fits the constraints)
- Licence type (open-source / free / commercial)
- Alternatives considered and why they were discarded

Cover at minimum: frontend framework, backend language/framework,
database, authentication mechanism, hosting/deployment approach,
and reporting/export capability.
```

---

## 💬 Prompt 3 — Component design

```
Describe each system component in detail.

For each component provide:
- Component name
- Layer it belongs to
- Responsibility (what it does)
- Interfaces (what it exposes or consumes)
- Dependencies on other components

Components to cover as a minimum:
- User Interface (web frontend)
- Authentication module
- Reservation management module
- Resource management module
- Notification module
- Reporting module
- Administration module
- Database layer
```

---

## 💬 Prompt 4 — Data model

```
Design the data model for the system.

For each entity provide:
- Entity name
- Attributes (name, data type, constraints)
- Primary key
- Foreign keys and relationships to other entities

Entities to cover as a minimum:
- User
- Role
- Location
- Resource
- ResourceType
- TimeSlot
- Reservation
- ReservationStatus
- Notification
- AuditLog
- ReservationRule

Present the relationships between entities clearly,
indicating cardinality (one-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many).
```

---

## 💬 Prompt 5 — Security design

```
Describe the security design of the system covering:

- Authentication mechanism (how users prove their identity)
- Session management (how authenticated sessions are maintained and expired)
- Authorization model (how role-based access is enforced at the component level)
- Data protection measures (patron personal data)
- Input validation and protection against common web vulnerabilities
- Audit logging strategy

Map each security measure to the relevant non-functional requirements
(NFR-008 through NFR-011).
```

---

## 💬 Prompt 6 — Deployment and infrastructure

```
Describe the deployment architecture for the system considering:

- Hosting approach (on-premise vs cloud vs hybrid) with justification
  based on the budget and infrastructure constraints
- Environment strategy (development, testing, production)
- Backup and recovery approach
- How the system will be accessed from the three library locations
- Estimated infrastructure requirements (server specs, storage)
- Approach to go-live with no prolonged downtime

Map recommendations to NFR-006, NFR-007, NFR-022 and NFR-023.
```

